.TH "iwl_sta_id_or_broadcast" 9 "iwl_sta_id_or_broadcast" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iwl_sta_id_or_broadcast \- return sta_id or broadcast sta
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iwl_sta_id_or_broadcast
.BI "(struct iwl_rxon_context *context "  ","
.BI "struct ieee80211_sta *sta "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "context" 12
the current context
.IP "sta" 12
mac80211 station
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
In certain circumstances mac80211 passes a station pointer
that may be NULL, for example during TX or key setup. In
that case, we need to use the broadcast station, so this
inline wraps that pattern.
